## 4. FINANCIAL SNAPSHOT (5-Year Trends)

### Revenue Growth Trajectory

| Fiscal Year | Revenue (USD) | YoY Growth | Advanced Tech % | HPC % | Gross Margin |
|-------------|--------------|-----------|----------------|-------|-------------|
| **FY21** | $56.8B | +25% | 50% | 37% | 51.6% |
| **FY22** | $75.9B | +34% | 54% | 41% | 59.4% |
| **FY23** | $69.3B | -9% | 58% | 43% | 54.4% |
| **FY24** | $90.1B | +30% | 69% | 51% | 56.1% |
| **FY25** | $122.4B | +36% | 74% | 55% | 59.9% |
| **FY26E** | $159.0B | +30% | 78% | 58% | 62.0% |

**Key Inflection:** FY24-25 marked AI infrastructure buildout acceleration, reversing FY23 cyclical downturn

### Profitability Expansion

| Metric | FY22 | FY23 | FY24 | FY25 | FY26E |
|--------|------|------|------|------|-------|
| **Gross Margin** | 59.4% | 54.4% | 56.1% | 59.9% | 62.0% |
| **Operating Margin** | 49.1% | 42.0% | 45.7% | 50.8% | 53.5% |
| **Net Margin** | 42.2% | 37.8% | 40.6% | 45.1% | 47.0% |
| **ROE** | 28.9% | 25.3% | 30.3% | 35.4% | ~38% |
| **ROIC** | ~32% | ~27% | ~31% | ~35% | ~36% |

**Margin Drivers:**
- FY23 Contraction: Inventory correction, crypto collapse, consumer weakness (smartphones/PCs)
- FY24-25 Expansion: AI demand inflection, advanced node mix shift (54% → 74%)
- FY26 Acceleration: 2nm ramp (highest margins), operating leverage, FX tailwinds (TWD 31.6 assumption)

### Balance Sheet Fortress

| Item | FY24 | FY25 | Q1 FY26E |
|------|------|------|----------|
| **Cash & Equivalents** | $40.8B | $51.5B | $48.0B |
| **Total Debt** | $31.1B | $32.5B | $33.0B |
| **Net Cash** | $9.7B | $19.0B | $15.0B |
| **Shareholder Equity** | $162.4B | $189.2B | $198.0B |
| **Debt/Equity** | 19% | 17% | 17% |

**Capital Efficiency:**
- Negative working capital: Customers prepay for capacity allocations
- Capex Intensity: 35-40% of revenue (industry-leading efficiency)
- ROIC: 35%+ despite massive capital deployment

### Cash Flow Generation

| Metric | FY23 | FY24 | FY25 | FY26E |
|--------|------|------|------|-------|
| **Operating Cash Flow** | $40.8B | $55.8B | $79.2B | $95.0B |
| **Capex** | $30.4B | $29.8B | $38.0B | $56.0B |
| **Free Cash Flow** | $10.4B | $26.0B | $41.2B | $39.0B |
| **FCF Margin** | 15% | 29% | 34% | 25% |

**FY26 FCF Compression:** Peak capex cycle ($56B) temporarily reduces FCF despite revenue growth

**Cash Deployment:**
- Dividends: TWD 18/share (FY25) → TWD 23+/share (FY26) = $10-12B annually
- Buybacks: Minimal (capital prioritized for capacity expansion)
- Capex: 70-80% advanced nodes, 10-20% advanced packaging, 10% specialty

